title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1978-10-20
lineage: 2 x AKG D224e => Sony TC-158 >> MAC,Analog Sound Preservation: MAC >> Nakamichi CR-7a => Korg MR-1000 DSF >> Korg MR-1000 => Korg AudioGate >> WAV [24/96] Taped By: Reinhart Holwein,Transfer By: Bob Menke,Mastering By: Derek McCabe
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Dire Wolf, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, It's All Over Now, Loser, Lazy Lightning > Supplication

Set 2

Mississippi Half-Step Uptown Toodeloo > Franklin's Tower, Dancin' In The Streets > Drums > Space > Not Fade Away > Black Peter > Around & Around 

E1: Johnny B. Goode 

E2: Shakedown Street

reviews.review_text:
another gem from winterland This night might get over looked because of the other nights with the from Egypt with love but this is one that everyone should have a copy of and this recording has it all. soundboard aud mixes are something I love only cause whats a dead show with us in the crowd.  Grab this ASAP 

ONLY 4 STARS BECAUSE THE OTHER NIGHTS ARE THE 5'S
